| **fs_move** | Move / rename a workspace path | Rename a file or relocate it under a different subdir. Both endpoints must stay inside the project workspace. |
| **fs_copy** | Copy a workspace file or directory tree | Promote a scratch file to evidence (e.g. `notes/probe.txt` -> `tool-outputs/findings.txt`) before further edits, or duplicate an offloaded result for safe modification. |
| **fs_mkdir** | Create a workspace directory | Pre-create an output subtree before writing many files into it. Default subdirs (notes/, tool-outputs/, jobs/, uploads/) are auto-created on first access; you only need fs_mkdir for custom layouts. |
| **fs_chmod** | Change permission bits on a workspace file | Make a payload script executable before running it through kali_shell. Auditable + parameter-validated alternative to `kali_shell chmod`. |
| **fs_symlink_create** | Create a symlink inside the workspace | Stable shortcut to a frequently-referenced offloaded file or wordlist. Both target and link must resolve inside the workspace. |
| **fs_grep** | Ripgrep over the workspace (or a subtree of it) | Find specific strings across many offloaded files, search inside a running job's log (jobs/<id>.log), narrow a huge tool output to relevant lines before fs_read. |
| **fs_glob** | Find w
