| **fs_read** | Read a file from the project workspace with line numbers | Inspect a file you wrote earlier or that was produced by an offloaded tool result. ALWAYS use this to drill into tool-outputs/ files after seeing an [Output offloaded:] marker. |
| **fs_read_many** | Batched read of multiple workspace files with a hard total-payload cap | Triage N small files in one call (N <= ~50). Each file is delimited by `=== <path> ===`; reading stops when `max_total_bytes` is reached. |
| **fs_stat** | Filesystem metadata (size, mtime, mode, type) with optional sha256 | Confirm a file exists / check size before reading; record evidence integrity hashes; spot symlinks. |
| **fs_write** | Atomic create / overwrite / append a workspace file | Save notes, intermediate findings, payload files, evidence. Three modes: `overwrite` (default, atomic via tmp+rename), `create_only` (errors if exists), `append`. |
| **fs_edit** | Exact-string replacement in a workspace file with uniqueness check | Surgical edit to an existing file. Errors if `old_string` matches multiple times unless `replace_all=True`. Pushes a snapshot onto an undo stack. |
| **fs_multi_edit** | Multiple ordered edits to one file, all-or-nothing | Apply N coordinated changes to a single file atomically. If ANY edit fails its uniqueness check, NO changes land. Prefer over N sequential fs_edit calls when the edits are related. |
| **fs_undo_edit** | Revert the most recent fs_edit / fs_multi_edit on a file | Roll back an edit you made earlier in the same session. Undo history is in-memory only (lost on agent restart) and capped at 20 snapshots per file. |
| **fs_delete** | Delete a workspace file or directory | Remove obsolete scratch / failed-experiment files. For directories you MUST pass `recursive=True` (safety default). |
| **fs_move** | Move / rename a workspace path | Rename a file or relocate it under a different subdir. Both endpoints must stay inside the project workspace. |
| **fs_copy** | Copy a workspace file or directory tree | Promote a scratch file to evidence (e.g. `notes/probe.txt` -> `tool-outputs/findings.txt`) before further edits, or duplicate an offloaded result for safe modification. |
| **fs_mkdir** | Create a workspace directory | Pre-create an output subtree before writing many files into it. Default subdirs (notes/, tool-outputs/, jobs/, uploads/) are auto-created on first access; you only need fs_mkdir for custom layouts. |
| **fs_chmod** | Change permission bits on a workspace file | Make a payload script executable before running it through kali_shell. Auditable + parameter-validated alternative to `kali_shell chmod`. |
| **fs_symlink_create** | Create a symlink inside the workspace | Stable shortcut to a frequently-referenced offloaded file or wordlist. Both target and link must resolve inside the workspace. |
| **fs_grep** | Ripgrep over the workspace (or a subtree of it) | Find specific strings across many offloaded files, search inside a running job's log (jobs/<id>.log), narrow a huge tool output to relevant lines before fs_read. |
| **fs_glob** | Find w
