orkspace files by glob pattern, sorted newest-first | Locate files when you know the name pattern but not the exact path (e.g. `*.json`, `**/findings-*.txt`). Sorted by mtime descending so the most-recently-written hits come first. |
| **fs_find** | Metadata-based file search (name pattern + mtime + size + type filters) | When glob alone is not enough - filter by recency (mtime=<1h), size (size=>10M), or type (file/dir/symlink). |
| **fs_list** | Single-directory listing with type indicator, size, mtime | Look inside one specific directory. Use fs_tree for a hierarchical view, fs_glob/fs_find for pattern-based search. |
| **fs_tree** | Depth-limited ASCII tree of a workspace subtree | Get oriented in an unfamiliar subdir or after a scan dumps many files. Skips .git / node_modules / __pycache__ / hidden dirs. |
| **fs_symbols** | AST outline of a source file (functions / classes / methods + line ranges) | Quick orientation in a code file (e.g. a JS reconnaissance script, a Python payload) without reading the whole thing. Supports 15 languages. |
| **fs_symlink_read** | Resolve a symlink to its raw target | Inspect what a symlink points at WITHOUT following it (fs_read/fs_stat would resolve through it). Useful to spot symlink-escape attempts in scan output. |
| **fs_hash** | Compute sha256 or md5 of a workspace file | Evidence integrity (record before/after hashes), IoC matching, dedupe across multiple scan runs. |
