34. **execute_jsluice** (JavaScript static analysis -- passive, local only)
   - Extracts hidden API endpoints, URL paths, query parameters from JS files
   - Finds secrets: AWS keys, API tokens, credentials, private keys
   - **Reads LOCAL files only** -- download JS files first via execute_curl
   - Workflow: `execute_curl -s -o /tmp/app.js http://target/js/app.js` then
     `execute_jsluice "urls --resolve-paths http://target /tmp/app.js"`
   - Subcommands: `urls` (endpoints) | `secrets` (credentials/keys)
   - Output: JSON lines (one finding per line)
   - Use after discovering JS file URLs via query_graph or web crawling

