| **fs_symbols** | AST outline of a source file (functions / classes / methods + line ranges) | Quick orientation in a code file (e.g. a JS reconnaissance script, a Python payload) without reading the whole thing. Supports 15 languages. |
| **fs_symlink_read** | Resolve a symlink to its raw target | Inspect what a symlink points at WITHOUT following it (fs_read/fs_stat would resolve through it). Useful to spot symlink-escape attempts in scan output. |
| **fs_hash** | Compute sha256 or md5 of a workspace file | Evidence integrity (record before/after hashes), IoC matching, dedupe across multiple scan runs. |
| **fs_diff** | Unified diff between two workspace files OR a file and its last fs_read snapshot | Compare two files; OR with `vs_last_read=True`, detect whether a file changed since your most recent fs_read (closes the stale-read race when multiple fireteam agents share the workspace). |
| **fs_extract** | Extract a tar / zip / gz archive into the workspace, with zip-slip / tar-slip protection | Unpack nuclei templates, wordlists, evidence archives a user dropped into uploads/. |
| **fs_archive** | Bundle workspace paths into a tar.gz or zip | Package evidence for one-click download from the FS drawer, or assemble a multi-file payload before exfil. |
| **job_spawn** | Detach a tool call to run as a background asyncio task | When a tool will take longer than a single agent turn (deep nuclei scans, hydra brute force, slow exploitation). Returns immediately with a job_id; the agent's turn is free to keep working or yield to the user. |
| **job_status** | Query a job's current status, size, and tail | Poll without blocking. Returns the current status (`running|done|failed|cancelled|interrupted`), size of log file, last 40 lines of output. |
| **job_wait** | Block up to N seconds waiting for a job to complete | Chunk a long wait. Call repeatedly with `timeout_sec=30` so you yield control between waits and the user can interrupt. |
| **job_cancel** | Cancel a running job and flip its status to `cancelled` | User says stop / scan is taking too long / you realise the args were wrong. |
| **job_list** | List background jobs in the current project | See what is running / has run. Filter by `active=True` (running only) or `active=False` (terminal only). |
