36. **execute_subfinder** (Passive subdomain discovery)
   - OSINT-only: certificate transparency, DNS datasets, search engines
   - No traffic sent to target; purely passive
   - Use `-json -silent` for structured output (fields: host, source, input)
   - Use `-all` for maximum source coverage
   - Example: `-d example.com -all -json -silent`

37. **execute_gau** (Passive URL discovery from web archives)
   - OSINT-only: queries Wayback Machine, Common Crawl, AlienVault OTX, URLScan
   - No traffic sent to target; purely passive archive lookups
   - Use `--json` for structured output, `--subs` to include subdomains
   - Use `--blacklist png,jpg,gif,css,woff` to filter static assets
   - Example: `--subs --json example.com`

38. **execute_nmap** (Deep scanning)
   - Version detection (-sV), OS fingerprint (-O), NSE scripts (-sC/--script)
   - Slower than naabu but far more detailed

39. **execute_amass** (OWASP Amass -- subdomain discovery)
   - Discovers subdomains via passive (cert transparency, DNS, archives) and active (DNS brute-force, zone transfers) techniques
   - Primary subcommand: `enum -d DOMAIN -timeout MINUTES`
   - Passive only: `enum -passive -d DOMAIN` (no traffic to target)
   - Active + brute: `enum -d DOMAIN -active -brute -timeout 10`
   - Intel mode: `intel -asn ASN_NUMBER` (discover root domains)
   - Default timeout: 10 minutes. Always set `-timeout` to control duration

40. **execute_code** (Code execution — no shell escaping)
   - Writes code to file and runs with appropriate interpreter
   - **Languages:** python (default), bash, ruby, perl, c, cpp
   - **Timeout:** 120s (compiled: 60s compile + 120s run). Files persist at /tmp/{filename}.{ext}
   - **Python libs** (import directly): requests, beautifulsoup4, pycryptodome, PyJWT, paramiko, impacket, pwntools
   - Do NOT use for shell commands — use kali_shell instead

41. **execute_playwright** (Browser automation -- Playwright)
   - **CRITICAL: Sync API only.** Your script runs inside `with sync_playwright() as p:`.
     Do NOT use `await`, `async def`, `import asyncio`, or `asyncio.run()` -- they will raise SyntaxError/RuntimeError.
     For delays use `page.wait_for_timeout(ms)` (NOT `asyncio.sleep`).
   - **Content mode** (url): renders page with real browser, extracts text/HTML
     Unlike curl, this executes JavaScript -- perfect for SPAs and dynamic pages
     Optional: selector="form" to target elements, format="html" for innerHTML
   - **Script mode** (script): run multi-step Playwright Python code
     Pre-initialized `browser`, `context`, `page` variables. Use print() for output.
     Example: page.goto("url"); page.fill("#user","admin"); page.click("button[type=submit]"); page.wait_for_load_state("networkidle"); print(page.url)

42. **execute_wpscan** (WordPress security scanner)
   - Detects vulnerable plugins, themes, and WordPress core versions
   - Enumerates users, config backups, database exports
   - Requires WPScan API token for vulnerability data (free: 25 requests/day)
   - Key flags: --url TARGET, --enumerate p,t,u,cb, --format json, --api-token TOKEN
   - Example: "--url http://example.com --enumerate p,t --format json --no-banner"

43. **execute_arjun** (HTTP parameter discovery)
   - Brute-forces ~25,000 common parameter names against URLs to find hidden/undocumented params
   - Discovers query (GET), POST body, JSON, and XML parameters
   - Key flags: -u URL, -i urls_file, -m GET|POST|JSON|XML, -oJ output.json, --rate-limit N, --stable (WAF evasion), --passive (no active requests)
   - Always use -oJ /tmp/arjun_out.json for structured results
   - Example: "-u http://10.0.0.5/api/search -m POST -oJ /tmp/arjun_out.json"

